Lady Biba is that indigenous Ready to wear Fashion brand that caters to women fondly tagged ” Lady Bosses” across all business sectors and industries. For the past seven years, the Lady Biba brand has been dedicated to meeting the needs of professional women who desire to stand out and make a statement in a modern and simple yet stylish way via its online store.  Recently, the brand has expanded its horizons by launching its first-ever walk-in store. The store opening which launched on the September 1st, indeed created a delightful shopping experience as it featured numerous Influencers and fashionistas alike, cutting across the entertainment, media and economic sector, as they all gathered to shop select pieces and styles. Guests were also catered to yummy canapés from Bread lounge and Drinks from Absolut Nigeria.  The retail store caters to women within their 20’s to ’50s providing variety in work-wear options to suit all personality styles and ensures to leave all that shop feeling like a Lady Boss. The event was supported by Scentimentals, Taos Cosmetics, Kuddy Cosmetics, Bread Lounge, Moabi, and Absolut Nigeria as well as fashion site, Bellanaija style as media partner.  The store is situated at 13, Taiye Olowu street, off Victoria Arobieke Street, Lekki phase one.
It’s opening hours are:
Monday through Friday by 10:00 am to 6:00 pm.
Saturday 11:00am to 5:00pm
Fittings by Appointment on Friday and Saturday by 11:00 am to 4:00 pm. The store will also have a massive Pre-independence day sales from Friday, September 27th to Tuesday, October 1st with a clearance sales of up to 20% to 50% off on each purchase.  —————————————————————————————————————————————– Sponsored Content The post Lady Biba Launches its First Retail Store In Lagos 🎉 appeared first on BellaNaija – Showcasing Africa to the world. Read today!. Source: Bella Naija